{"name":"Shadow Hunter","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/light/projectile-beam-yellow-blue.webp","system":{"description":"<p>You have learned the weakness of Sherazade's Shadows—those OL 5, 1 Wound copies of past enemies with Shadow Body Gifts. Shadows can appear and disappear from darkness (+1 OL in shadows), regenerate unless in full light, and are only permanently destroyed by direct sunlight. With this Gift: (1) You can force Shadows to manifest by creating bright light (lanterns, magic, fire)—they cannot use Shadow Body while you illuminate them. (2) Once per Scene, make an opposed Check vs a Shadow's OL 5: on success, you've maneuvered it into a sunbeam, moonbeam through window, or reflected light—Shadow is destroyed permanently without Wound roll. (3) You recognize which past enemy a Shadow is copying, giving you +1 to Checks against it based on previous knowledge of its tactics.</p>","notes":"<p><strong>Requirement:</strong> Survive at least one encounter with Sherazade's Shadows and study their mechanics, OR research shadow-creature lore</p>\n<p><strong>Limitations:</strong> Requires light source to be effective—useless in total darkness. Creating bright light may alert other enemies. Sunlight destruction only works if you can create/find actual sunlight (challenging indoors or at night). Some locations Sherazade chooses for confrontations have no windows or light sources—plan accordingly.</p>\n<p><strong>Tags:</strong> combat, light, knowledge, anti-shadow</p>","key":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.shadow-hunter","owner":"","category":"Scenario Gift","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares"},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.shadow-hunter","scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","sourceLanguage":"en","legacySource":"E:/respaldos/brokentales-repo/packs/actors/scenario-gifts/one-thousand-and-one-nightmares/Shadow Hunter.json"}},"_id":"NQEdtGc4xI2MBAEj","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"name":"Story Breaker","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-pentagon-orange.webp","system":{"description":"<p>Sherazade traps victims inside stories—either locking them in narrative loops where they relive false memories, or creating 'what-if' scenarios that never happened. You've learned to recognize when you're inside a story rather than reality. Watch for narrative inconsistencies: characters acting wrong, impossible events, details that don't match your memories. Once per Scene when trapped in a story, make a Mental Check vs Sherazade's OL 7: on success, you break the narrative—story shatters like glass and you return to reality, immune to story imprisonment for rest of Scene. On failure, you're deeper in the story and must find its 'ending' before you can escape (GM creates story-specific exit condition). You can also attempt to free ONE other trapped victim when you break out.</p>","notes":"<p><strong>Requirement:</strong> Be trapped in at least one of Sherazade's stories and escape, OR witness someone else trapped and deduce the pattern</p>\n<p><strong>Limitations:</strong> Requires Mental Check each time—repeated story trapping becomes harder to break. Some stories are more seductive than reality (what-if where loved one never died)—GM may impose disadvantage if story offers something you desperately want. Breaking story while others remain trapped may anger them (they don't realize it's false). Sherazade adapts—after you break first story, her subsequent stories are more complex (higher OL or multiple layers).</p>\n<p><strong>Tags:</strong> mental, escape, anti-narrative, reality</p>","key":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.story-breaker","owner":"","category":"Scenario Gift","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares"},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.story-breaker","scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","sourceLanguage":"en","legacySource":"E:/respaldos/brokentales-repo/packs/actors/scenario-gifts/one-thousand-and-one-nightmares/Story Breaker.json"}},"_id":"VFlPxvlgDPsYAez8","sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"name":"Truth Beneath Tales","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-tendrils-orange.webp","system":{"description":"<p>Sherazade's Gift 'Words like Honey' makes her incredibly persuasive and believable—people trust her instinctively, follow her suggestions, believe her lies. You've learned to see through her narrative manipulation by focusing on actions rather than words. When Sherazade or her Shadows attempt social manipulation, persuasion, or deception against you, you gain +2 to resist (effectively reducing her OL from 7 to 5 for Social Checks targeting you). Additionally, once per Scene, you can point out a contradiction in her story to one NPC: make a Social Check vs her OL 7—on success, that NPC becomes immune to her Words like Honey for this Scene and may turn against her. This represents your ability to find truth buried beneath beautiful lies.</p>","notes":"<p><strong>Requirement:</strong> Recognize Sherazade's Words like Honey Gift in action and study how she manipulates others, OR resist her manipulation successfully at least once</p>\n<p><strong>Limitations:</strong> Only protects YOU from social manipulation—allies remain vulnerable unless you spend action to free them. Pointing out contradictions may anger Sherazade, causing her to abandon subtlety and attack directly. Some NPCs are so deeply manipulated they refuse to believe evidence even when presented clearly. This Gift doesn't work against her other powers (story imprisonment, Shadow summoning)—only social manipulation.</p>\n<p><strong>Tags:</strong> social, perception, anti-manipulation, truth</p>","key":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.truth-beneath-tales","owner":"","category":"Scenario Gift","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares"},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.truth-beneath-tales","scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","sourceLanguage":"en","legacySource":"E:/respaldos/brokentales-repo/packs/actors/scenario-gifts/one-thousand-and-one-nightmares/Truth Beneath Tales.json"}},"_id":"QFc23hnzK6w7Snpl","sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0}}
